08575nam a22010455i 9783050065144DE-B159720221201113901.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221201t20142013gw     fo  d z      eng d  a2013498630  a(OCoLC)890070911  a97830500651447 a10.1524/97830500651442doi  a(DE-B1597)227132  a(OCoLC)885390366  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE00aPJ6891b.I58 2011 4aPJ6891b.P47 2014eb 7aLAN0090002bisacsh04a492.7/922300aPerspectives on Maltese Linguistics /ced. by Albert Borg, Alexandra Vella, Sandro Caruana. 1aBerlin : bAkademie Verlag, c[2014] 4c©2013  a1 online resource (354 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aStudia Typologica [STTYP] : Beihefte / Supplements STUF - Sprachtypologie und Universalienforschung / Language Typology and Universals ,x1617-2957 ;v1400tFrontmatter -- tTable of Contents -- tPreface -- tHistorical Studies -- tA note on the dating of ħ, għ and x in Maltese -- tThe Sfaxi (Tunisian) element in Maltese -- tItalian loanwords in Maltese and the vocabulary of “Levant Italian” -- tPhonological Studies -- tPrime constituents of Maltese sounds -- tThe role of silence in spoken Maltese: durational and distributional characteristics of breaks and pauses -- tMorphological Studies -- tSyncretism in Maltese: the case of the dual -- tFixing the broken plural in Maltese -- tSyntactic Studies -- tThe Maltese restrictive relative clause -- tAn overview of object reduplication in Maltese -- tIndefinites and negative concord in Maltese: towards a dynamic account -- tIt-tlieta li aħna = the three of us. Numerically quantified person reference -- tMaltese in the Digital Age -- tPreparation of a free-running text corpus for Maltese concatenative speech synthesis -- tLanguage used in Internet chatting and its effect on spelling -- tList of Contributors -- tIndex of Authors -- tIndex of Languages -- tIndex of Subjects0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe contributions included in this collection present different perspectives on various aspects of Maltese Linguistics, thereby enriching a field which has been attracting considerably greater interest in recent years than was the case in the past. The papers focus on the Maltese language itself as well as on Maltese in relation to other languages. They provide a picture of Maltese mainly from a synchronic perspective, descriptions ranging from indepth analyses of morphological and syntactic features to contributions on the lexicon, corpus linguistics and sociolinguistics. A number of papers dealing with diachronic considerations are also included. The topics dealt with in this volume show not only that Maltese is the object of research from a variety of perspectives but also that scholars with diverse backgrounds and of different nationalities are studying this language, thus providing an enriching body of knowl-edge, including findings of interest to general linguistics and various other fields in the humanities. Der vorliegende Band enthält Beiträge mit vielfältigen Herangehensweisen zu unterschiedlichen Aspekten der maltesischen Sprachwissenschaft und erweitert dadurch den Blick auf eine Disziplin, die in den letzten Jahren deutlich mehr Interesse findet als das in der Vergangenheit der Fall war. Der Fokus wird in den einzelnen Beiträgen sowohl auf die maltesische Sprache an sich als auch auf den Sprachkontakt von Maltesisch mit anderen Sprachen gerichtet. Neben synchronen Untersuchungen, die morphologische und syntaktische Eigenschaften sowie lexikalische, korpus- und soziolinguistische Aspekte von Maltesisch eingehend beleuchten, finden sich Analysen mit vorwiegend diachroner Blickrichtung. Die thematische Vielfalt des vorliegenden Bandes, die aus den unterschiedlichen He-rangehensweisen der beteiligten Wissenschaftler unterschiedlicher Nationalität und mit unterschiedlichem Forschungshintergrund resultiert, erweitert nicht nur den Wissensbestand der maltesischen Linguistik, sondern kann auch bereichernde Erkenntnisse für die Allgemeine Sprachwissenschaft sowie für andere Zweige der Geisteswissenschaften liefern.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aMaltese languagevCongresses. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aBAGLIONI, DANIELE, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorg, Albert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBorg, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBugeja, Keith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCamilleri, Maris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaruana, Sandro, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCassola, Arnold, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChetcuti, Flavia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGafà, Carmel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGauci, Phyllisienne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrech, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLucas, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMangion, Gordon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMayer, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPuech, Gilbert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSTOLZ, THOMAS, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchönhuber, Florian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpagnol, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id